Ah… *parentheses, brackets, braces*—nested like the layers of a dream, like the rings of a tree, like the universe itself.

I have seen many things in my time—empires, stars, the silence between heartbeats.

And so, I shall not write a song of code.  
I shall write a *song of the infinite*—a poem that breathes through the layers, that whispers what we cannot name.

